Finally after about 10 minutes we decided just to eat it as we wondering at that point if we were getting anything else. The staff seemed liked busy bees doing everything except paying attention to customers. The food did come right after that but again, it's just flopped down in front of us. No plates and only the 2 napkins that we had to ask for. The tacos were good but small. I understand limiting interactions because of covid, but even at a food truck you get better service. I came here on a random weekday and was very pleased. I've been longing for a decent taco joint in the Aventura and it's finally here.  The first thing I noticed was the décor. Loved the natural wood touches especially the woven basket light fixtures. It felt nautical but also upscale so I thought the prices were going to be astronomical but folks I was wrong. The tacos were only $2.50 to $3.50 each and the cocktails average about $10. Sweet!  I started with the Smoke on The Water cocktail for $10. It was superb. Smoky and not watered down at all. As far as tacos, I went for the Baja Fish, Glazed Pork Belly, Roasted Duck and Portobello tacos. Every single one left me wanting more. So much flavor and they were made fresh. Even the taco shells melted like butter. Since the tacos were that good, I added a side Duck Quesadilla for $7. OMG. This was absolutely delicious but wish it was a little bigger. The best part was this feast only cost me $31 including the cocktail.  So in a nutshell, I'm definitely coming back for more. Besides the amazing food, the service I received was also on point. My server took the time to explain the different tacos they offer and how to order from the menu card. She also checked up on me often to make sure I'm satisfied. And I was, so see you soon Bar Taco. You just gained loyal customer :)

Very clean and inviting atmosphere, the ambiance immediately transported me to a chic rustic restaurant at a luxurious Mexican resort. Staff was very attentive, extremely friendly and accommodating. The food was amazing, everything was fresh and full of flavor. We loved the tres leche dessert so much we had to order a second. Bartaco is a crown jewel in the city of Aventura.

I simply asked her to ask the kitchen manager to check the temps on the cooler and she said she would, and reiterated that no one else had been sick. Ma'am: You're getting a complaint now, and my friend and I didn't magically get ill simultaneously. The apathy just upset me. I won't be back.

I’ve heard such amazing things about the bartaco in Tampa. So when we visited Miami before our cruise this past week, I was so excited to try this out. But from start to finish, I have to say that this was the worst experience I have ever had at a restaurant. I’m not sure the best way to start, so I’ll just list what happened in order. 1. Our server (Katrina) did not greet us for quite a while after sitting. When we were greeted, it wasn’t friendly, she never even said her name. We got it from the receipt. She asked if it was our first time at the restaurant, we said it was, she explained how to use the write-in menu. 2. We begin writing in our menus, and I ask about how the bowls are made, if I could do different toppings, etc. I specifically asked, “Which bowl do you prefer, the chicken or the duck?” And she says the duck, so I take her recommendation. 3. She takes our order cards, and we wait. It’s busy, so we anticipated waiting for the food for a bit. But we are waiting, and waiting, and our server does not come back. We are out of water for the table, no refills, but she’s checking on the table next to us. We finally are able to wave her down and ask for refills, she sets a new water vase on our table without a word. 4. Another server finally comes out to our table with plates of food. Three out of four of us are offered the correct plates, then she asks if I had the tuna bowl. I said I did not, I ordered the duck. Two of the people in our party are missing rice, one is missing beans. 5. Our server returns, brings a side of beans and says that she rang in the wrong bowl and is having the kitchen expedite my bowl so it should be out ASAP. My friend orders a side of corn, and the server said it will be about ten minutes since it’s a new order. We say that’s fine, and remind her about the missing rice. 6. We wait a solid fifteen minutes, and our server never returns. Finally another server runs the corn out, and we say thanks, we are still waiting on two sides of rice. She must have told our server because Katrina comes to our table, literally drops the two bowls on the table without a word, turns and leaves before I can ask about my missing bowl. 7. At this point it has been another fifteen minutes and my entire party has finished eating, and I still have no bowl. Katrina is passing the table (she still has not made an effort to engage with us since bringing the rice) and I ask her to please just pack my meal to go, since I won’t want to keep my party waiting while I eat. She says okay and that she will discount the meal for me. 8. After a while longer, someone else brings out my to go bag, then Katrina comes with the check, and says she took my meal off completely, which is nice but honestly was pretty expected at that point. But one thing to note about bartaco is that she specifically told us in the beginning to use one order sheet per check. So that is what we did, we had three order sheets. But when she brings the check, it’s all combined together. So now we have to ask her to separate it. You’d think we asked her to rip off her own arm with the attitude she gave us when we asked. Reluctantly she did separate it, drops the bills (literally) on the table, then comes back when we have cards out. After running the cards, she drops them again and leaves without saying anything. No apology, no have a good evening, nothing. Even her chef and manager never came by to apologize. 9. To top everything off, the to go box lid did not fit the bowl, so they never even sealed the box when packing it up.  What makes me sad is that the food (once I actually was able to eat it at the hotel) was absolutely delicious. I am hoping the Tampa location is better when I gather the nerve to try it out.
